Class ImplClassStructure

java.lang.Object
info.kgeorgiy.ja.chulkov.implementor.ImplInterfaceStructure
info.kgeorgiy.ja.chulkov.implementor.ImplClassStructure
public class ImplClassStructure extends ImplInterfaceStructure
Structure that parse and keeps information about class to implement it. Generates string for class implementation by ImplInterfaceStructure.toString()

  • Method Details

    • getRequiredForImplementationMethods

      private static List<? extends MethodStructure> getRequiredForImplementationMethods(Class<?> token, String name)
      Generates list of required to implement methods and constructors. Merges three types of methods by signature:
      • all non-private constructors
      • all public abstract methods declared in all superclasses and interfaces
      • all non-public abstract methods, declared in all superclasses
      Parameters:
      token - super class token, that needs to be implemented
      name - of implemented class
      Returns:
      list of required to implement methods

    • compressReturnedTypes

      private static Stream<MethodStructure> compressReturnedTypes(Stream<MethodStructure> methods)
      Compress methods with same signature. Return one method with covariant type.
      Parameters:
      methods - stream of methods
      Returns:
      stream of compressed methods
